{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "lxxe:sirach.21",
    "translationId": "lxxe",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 21,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 21 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.21.1",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:1",
      "text": "My son, hast thou sinned? do so no more, but ask pardon for thy former sins.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.21.2",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:2",
      "text": "Flee from sin as from the face of a serpent: for if thou comest too near it, it will bite thee: the teeth thereof are as the teeth of a lion, slaying the souls of men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.21.3",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:3",
      "text": "All iniquity is as a two edged sword, the wounds whereof cannot be healed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.21.4",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:4",
      "text": "To terrify and do wrong will waste riches: thus the house of proud men shall be made desolate.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.21.5",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:5",
      "text": "A prayer out of a poor man’s mouth reacheth to the ears of God, and his judgement cometh speedily.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.21.6",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:6",
      "text": "He that hateth to be reproved is in the way of sinners: but he that feareth the Lord will repent from his heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.21.7",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:7",
      "text": "An eloquent man is known far and near; but a man of understanding knoweth when he slippeth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.21.8",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:8",
      "text": "He that buildeth his house with other men’s money is like one that gathereth himself stones for the tomb of his burial.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.21.9",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:9",
      "text": "The congregation of the wicked is like tow wrapped together: and the end of them is a flame of fire to destroy them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.21.10",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:10",
      "text": "The way of sinners is made plain with stones, but at the end thereof is the pit of hell.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.21.11",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:11",
      "text": "He that keepeth the law of the Lord getteth the understanding thereof: and the perfection of the fear of the Lord is wisdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.21.12",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:12",
      "text": "He that is not wise will not be taught: but there is a wisdom which multiplieth bitterness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.21.13",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:13",
      "text": "The knowledge of a wise man shall abound like a flood: and his counsel is like a pure fountain of life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.21.14",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:14",
      "text": "The inner parts of a fool are like a broken vessel, and he will hold no knowledge as long as he liveth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.21.15",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:15",
      "text": "If a skilful man hear a wise word, he will commend it, and add unto it: but as soon as one of no understanding heareth it, it displeaseth him, and he casteth it behind his back.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.21.16",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:16",
      "text": "The talking of a fool is like a burden in the way: but grace shall be found in the lips of the wise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.21.17",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:17",
      "text": "They enquire at the mouth of the wise man in the congregation, and they shall ponder his words in their heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.21.18",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:18",
      "text": "As is a house that is destroyed, so is wisdom to a fool: and the knowledge of the unwise is as talk without sense.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.21.19",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:19",
      "text": "Doctrine unto fools is as fetters on the feet, and like manacles on the right hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.21.20",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:20",
      "text": "A fool lifteth up his voice with laughter; but a wise man doth scarce smile a little.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.21.21",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:21",
      "text": "Learning is unto a wise man as an ornament of gold, and like a bracelet upon his right arm.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.21.22",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:22",
      "text": "A foolish man’s foot is soon in his neighbour’s house: but a man of experience is ashamed of him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.21.23",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:23",
      "text": "A fool will peep in at the door into the house: but he that is well nurtured will stand without.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.21.24",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:24",
      "text": "It is the rudeness of a man to hearken at the door: but a wise man will be grieved with the disgrace.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.21.25",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:25",
      "text": "The lips of talkers will be telling such things as pertain not unto them: but the words of such as have understanding are weighed in the balance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.21.26",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:26",
      "text": "The heart of fools is in their mouth: but the mouth of the wise is in their heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.21.27",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:27",
      "text": "When the ungodly curseth Satan, he curseth his own soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.21.28",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:28",
      "text": "A whisperer defileth his own soul, and is hated wheresoever he dwelleth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
